  "notes": "First-generation Jilin-1 satellites still on orbit, including the Shipin video series. Seeded for the Orbits surface on Florian's instruction (2026-07-05); fields await sourced fill by the weekly maintenance run. Weekly maintenance (2026-07-13): Wikipedia's Jilin-1 article states 'eight Jilin-1 Smart Video Satellites' for this early series, with the most recent launch in the series on 2018-01-19 (matching the already-sourced Kuaizhou/Long March 11 event of that date already in this file's events list, which had not previously been reflected in latest_launch_date, an inconsistency now corrected). first_launch_date (2015-10-07, Gunter's) left unchanged, still the earliest and canonical. EO spec extraction (2026-07-16): eoPortal's Jilin/Gaofen Constellation page states no figures for this early (2015) generation, only for later Gaofen/Kuanfu generations; Gunter's Jilin-1 Optical-A page used instead, already cited elsewhere in this profile. swath_km and revisit left absent: not stated on the cited page.",
